There is a real architecture mismatch in this checkout: `roko-core` already depends on `roko-runtime`, so adding or using `roko_core::RuntimeEvent` from `roko-runtime` would create or require a cycle. I’m going to keep the code compiling inside the allowed file scope and mark the architectural blocker directly in the implementation.
